Melania and President Trump wish those observing Rosh Hashanah a blessed and happy New Year. They acknowledge that this is a time of celebration and reflection for the Jewish community, as they engage in prayer and repentance leading up to Yom Kippur, the holiest day in Judaism. The blowing of the shofar symbolizes a new spiritual journey for the Jewish people. The President emphasizes the virtues of kindness, compassion, and love that can be incorporated into everyone's lives to better the nation. He encourages forming sincere bonds with people of all faiths to spread peace and prosperity. Melania and the President pray that those celebrating Rosh Hashanah develop a more meaningful relationship with God throughout the High Holy Days.